---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'safetywing', text: 'SafetyWing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'img-global', text: 'IMG Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'allianz-care', text: 'Allianz Care', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-differences', text: 'Coverage Differences', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'SafetyWing Review', href: '/providers/safetywing' },
  { title: 'IMG Global Review', href: '/providers/img-global' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Budget Insurance', href: '/best/budget-insurance' },
  { title: 'Digital Nomad Insurance', href: '/best/digital-nomad-insurance' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Insurance Type', safetywing: 'Travel medical', img: 'Health insurance', allianz: 'Health insurance' },
  { feature: 'Coverage Limit', safetywing: '$250,000', img: '$1M - $8M', allianz: '€1M - €3M' },
  { feature: 'Pre-existing Conditions', safetywing: 'Not covered', img: 'Underwritten', allianz: 'Underwritten' },
  { feature: 'Routine Care', safetywing: 'Limited', img: 'Yes', allianz: 'Yes' },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', safetywing: 'Crisis only', img: 'Limited', allianz: 'Enhanced' },
  { feature: 'Maternity', safetywing: 'Emergency only', img: 'Optional', allianz: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'Flexibility', safetywing: 'Monthly subscription', img: 'Annual plans', allianz: 'Annual plans' },
  { feature: 'Best For', safetywing: 'Young nomads', img: 'Mid-range needs', allianz: 'Comprehensive value' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single, Age 25', safetywing: '$45-55/mo', img: '$80-150/mo', allianz: '$100-160/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 35', safetywing: '$55-70/mo', img: '$120-200/mo', allianz: '$150-200/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 45', safetywing: '$80-100/mo', img: '$180-280/mo', allianz: '$200-280/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 30', safetywing: '$100-130/mo', img: '$200-320/mo', allianz: '$260-360/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="SafetyWing vs IMG vs Allianz: Best Budget Expat Insurance 2026"
  description="Compare affordable expat insurance options: SafetyWing, IMG Global, and Allianz Care. Find the right balance of coverage and cost for your budget."
  headline="SafetyWing vs IMG vs Allianz: Budget-Friendly Options Compared"
  subheadline="Three approaches to affordable expat coverage—from bare-bones travel medical to comprehensive value. Here's how to choose."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <h2 id="quick-verdict">Quick Verdict</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-amber-50 border-2 border-amber-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Cheapest Option</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">SafetyWing</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">$45/mo starting. Travel medical insurance. Great for young, healthy nomads who want basic coverage.</p>
      <a href="/go/safetywing" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get SafetyWing Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-neutral-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Middle Ground</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">IMG Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Real health insurance at competitive prices. Flexible options. Good customer service.</p>
      <a href="/go/img-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-neutral-700 hover:bg-neutral-800 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get IMG Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Value</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Allianz Care</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Comprehensive coverage at 10-20% below premium competitors. Best mental health benefits.</p>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    These three represent different philosophies: SafetyWing is cheap but limited, IMG is solid middle-ground health insurance, and Allianz is comprehensive coverage at value pricing. Your choice depends on your health needs, risk tolerance, and how much you're willing to pay.
  </p>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="safetywing">SafetyWing</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Cheapest</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Monthly Billing</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">No Commitment</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    SafetyWing is travel medical insurance, not full health insurance. It's designed for digital nomads who want emergency coverage without the cost of comprehensive plans. Starting at $45/month with no commitment, it's the cheapest way to get basic international coverage.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Lowest price ($45/mo starting)</li>
    <li>Monthly subscription—cancel anytime</li>
    <li>No commitment or annual contract</li>
    <li>Simple signup process</li>
    <li>Good for emergency/catastrophic coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Travel medical, not health insurance</li>
    <li>$250K coverage limit (low for serious illness)</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions not covered</li>
    <li>Limited routine care coverage</li>
    <li>Mental health: crisis situations only</li>
    <li>No maternity (except emergency childbirth)</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Young, healthy digital nomads who want cheap emergency coverage. Not suitable for anyone with chronic conditions or who needs comprehensive care.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/safetywing" class="inline-block bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get SafetyWing Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/safetywing" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="img-global">IMG Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-neutral-200 text-neutral-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Real Health Insurance</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-neutral-200 text-neutral-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Flexible Plans</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-neutral-200 text-neutral-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Good Service</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    IMG Global offers actual international health insurance at competitive prices. Unlike SafetyWing, IMG provides real coverage with higher limits, pre-existing condition options, and comprehensive benefits. It's the middle ground between basic travel insurance and premium plans.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Real health insurance (not travel medical)</li>
    <li>Coverage up to $8M annually</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions can be underwritten</li>
    <li>Multiple plan options for flexibility</li>
    <li>Good customer service reputation</li>
    <li>Competitive mid-range pricing</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Annual commitment required</li>
    <li>Network smaller than premium insurers</li>
    <li>Mental health coverage limited</li>
    <li>Digital experience less polished</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Expats who want real health insurance without premium pricing. Those with moderate healthcare needs who want flexibility in plan design.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/img-global" class="inline-block bg-neutral-700 hover:bg-neutral-800 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get IMG Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/img-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="allianz-care">Allianz Care</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Value</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Mental Health</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Major Insurer</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Allianz Care is comprehensive international health insurance from a major global insurer—at prices 10-20% below competitors like Cigna and Bupa. If you want real coverage from a trusted name without paying premium prices, Allianz delivers the best value.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Comprehensive coverage from major insurer</li>
    <li>10-20% cheaper than Cigna/Bupa</li>
    <li>Best mental health coverage of the three</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions underwritten fairly</li>
    <li>Strong European network</li>
    <li>Backed by Allianz SE (German reliability)</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>More expensive than SafetyWing/IMG</li>
    <li>Annual commitment required</li>
    <li>Claims processing slower than premium competitors</li>
    <li>App less polished than Cigna</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Expats who want comprehensive coverage at a competitive price. Those who value mental health benefits. Europeans and those living in Europe.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/allianz-care" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare All Three"
    description="Get personalized quotes from SafetyWing, IMG, and Allianz based on your specific needs."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing Comparison</h2>

  <p>
    The price differences are significant. SafetyWing costs roughly half what IMG charges, and Allianz costs more than both—but provides proportionally more coverage.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
    *Estimated ranges for standard plans excluding US coverage. SafetyWing prices are their Nomad Insurance product.
  </p>

  <h2 id="coverage-differences">Understanding the Coverage Differences</h2>

  <p>
    Price isn't everything—what you get for your money matters more. Here's what each tier actually covers:
  </p>

  <h3>SafetyWing: Emergency Coverage Only</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Covers accidents and sudden illnesses</li>
    <li>Hospital stays for emergencies</li>
    <li>$250K limit (a serious illness could exceed this)</li>
    <li>No routine checkups, no preventive care</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions completely excluded</li>
    <li>Think of it as catastrophic coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>IMG: Solid Health Insurance</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Covers routine and emergency care</li>
    <li>Up to $8M limits available</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions considered case-by-case</li>
    <li>Outpatient visits and prescriptions covered</li>
    <li>Optional maternity add-on</li>
    <li>Real health insurance, not travel medical</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Allianz: Comprehensive Coverage</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Everything IMG offers, plus more</li>
    <li>Enhanced mental health benefits</li>
    <li>Better pre-existing condition terms</li>
    <li>Larger network (850K+ providers)</li>
    <li>More generous limits on most benefits</li>
    <li>Backed by major global insurer</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="best-for">Which Is Best For You?</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose SafetyWing if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are young and healthy with no pre-existing conditions</li>
        <li>Just want emergency/catastrophic coverage</li>
        <li>Need month-to-month flexibility</li>
        <li>Are on a tight budget ($45-100/mo)</li>
        <li>Don't need routine care coverage</li>
        <li>Understand you're accepting limited coverage</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose IMG Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Want real health insurance, not travel medical</li>
        <li>Have moderate budget ($100-300/mo)</li>
        <li>Need routine care and preventive coverage</li>
        <li>Want flexibility in plan design</li>
        <li>Have minor pre-existing conditions to cover</li>
        <li>Value good customer service</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Allianz Care if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Want comprehensive coverage at competitive prices</li>
        <li>Need strong mental health benefits</li>
        <li>Live in or travel to Europe frequently</li>
        <li>Have pre-existing conditions needing coverage</li>
        <li>Want backing from a major global insurer</li>
        <li>Can afford slightly higher premiums for better coverage</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Is SafetyWing real health insurance?</h3>
  <p>
    No. SafetyWing is travel medical insurance—it covers emergencies and accidents but not routine care, pre-existing conditions, or ongoing treatment. It's fundamentally different from health insurance products like IMG and Allianz offer.
  </p>

  <h3>What happens if I get seriously ill with SafetyWing?</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing's $250K limit could be exceeded by a serious illness like cancer treatment or major surgery. If you anticipate any significant health needs, choose IMG or Allianz with higher limits. SafetyWing is for emergencies, not chronic care.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I upgrade from SafetyWing to real insurance later?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, but any conditions that developed while on SafetyWing would be pre-existing for your new policy. If you develop a chronic condition while on SafetyWing, getting coverage for it later becomes harder and more expensive.
  </p>

  <h3>Which has the best mental health coverage?</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care by a wide margin. SafetyWing only covers mental health crises (not ongoing care). IMG has limited mental health benefits. Allianz includes enhanced mental health coverage with more generous session limits.
  </p>

  <h3>Are pre-existing conditions covered?</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing: No. IMG: Depends on underwriting—some conditions may be covered, excluded, or covered with a waiting period. Allianz: Similar to IMG but generally more accommodating for stable, well-managed conditions.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Prices and coverage details change. We are not insurance brokers. Verify current information directly with each provider before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
